            {
              "id": "CVE-2022-42252",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "tomcat: request smuggling"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "If Apache Tomcat 8.5.0 to 8.5.82, 9.0.0-M1 to 9.0.67, 10.0.0-M1 to 10.0.26 or 10.1.0-M1 to 10.1.0 was configured to ignore invalid HTTP headers via setting rejectIllegalHeader to false (the default for 8.5.x only), Tomcat did not reject a request containing an invalid Content-Length header making a request smuggling attack possible if Tomcat was located behind a reverse proxy that also failed to reject the request with the invalid header."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-42252",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2022-42252\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core\nFixed Version: 8.5.83, 9.0.68, 10.0.27, 10.1.1\nLink: [CVE-2022-42252](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-42252)\nIf Apache Tomcat 8.5.0 to 8.5.82, 9.0.0-M1 to 9.0.67, 10.0.0-M1 to 10.0.26 or 10.1.0-M1 to 10.1.0 was configured to ignore invalid HTTP headers via setting rejectIllegalHeader to false (the default for 8.5.x only), Tomcat did not reject a request containing an invalid Content-Length header making a request smuggling attack possible if Tomcat was located behind a reverse proxy that also failed to reject the request with the invalid header.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2022-42252**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-core|8.5.83, 9.0.68, 10.0.27, 10.1.1|[CVE-2022-42252](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-42252)|\n\nIf Apache Tomcat 8.5.0 to 8.5.82, 9.0.0-M1 to 9.0.67, 10.0.0-M1 to 10.0.26 or 10.1.0-M1 to 10.1.0 was configured to ignore invalid HTTP headers via setting rejectIllegalHeader to false (the default for 8.5.x only), Tomcat did not reject a request containing an invalid Content-Length header making a request smuggling attack possible if Tomcat was located behind a reverse proxy that also failed to reject the request with the invalid header."
              },
